<b>The scoop - </b>7/25/01 1:28:09 PM<br>~ <b>Kenross</b><blockquote>This song, like the level 50 song, was originally designed as a mana drain song.  Bards complained about the uselessness of a mana drain song as weak as these were, so Verant changed them to Haste/AC.  Normally, the Haste rules permit one item and one song/spell to stack.  All others are ignored.  This song (and the 50 song) is the exception - it stacks on top of the item/spell combo.  It was supposedly designed to allow people to exceed the Haste cap, but testing suggests that this is not true.<br><br>It is a Haste/AC song.<br></blockquote></td></tr><tr bgcolor="#eeeeee"><td>
